---------------------------------------------  DML COMAND-UPDATE -------------------------------------------------------------


Q.1) UPDATE THE PRICE OF A PARTICULAR PRODUCT

mysql> select * from products;
+-----+----------+--------+
| pid | pname    | price  |
+-----+----------+--------+
| 101 | pen      |  10.00 |
| 102 | boost    |  60.00 |
| 103 | horlicks | 120.00 |
| 104 | complan  |  78.00 |
| 105 | oats     |  45.00 |
+-----+----------+--------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

mysql> update products set price=100 where pid=103;
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.07 sec)
Rows matched: 1  Changed: 1  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from products;
+-----+----------+--------+
| pid | pname    | price  |
+-----+----------+--------+
| 101 | pen      |  10.00 |
| 102 | boost    |  60.00 |
| 103 | horlicks | 100.00 |
| 104 | complan  |  78.00 |
| 105 | oats     |  45.00 |
+-----+----------+--------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


